You must submit a confirmation from the Norwegian Child Welfare Service (barnevernet), because you have stated that {barn} is a foster child. {linjeskift} {linjeskift} The confirmation must show:

The date on which the child moved to you The date on which it was decided that you should have the care of the child.

You must submit documentation confirming that {barn} lives with you on a permanent basis, because the child(ren) is not registered in the Norwegian National Registry (folkeregisteret) with the same residential address as you. {linjeskift} {linjeskift} The confirmation must show that the child(ren) lives with you on a permanent basis and from which date. {linjeskift}{linjeskift}Examples of valid confirmation:

Written agreement between the parents on permanent residence Court document Confirmation from the child's school, kindergarten or the Child Welfare Service (barnevernet)
dokumentasjon.deltbosted.informasjon:
You must submit an agreement on dual residence because you have stated that dual residence has been agreed for {barn}. {linjeskift} {linjeskift} The agreement must include:

The names of the children it applies to The date from which the agreement is effective That the child is to have dual residence Both parents' signatures

You must submit a court document if dual residence has been decided by a court ruling.
dokumentasjon.deltbosted.vedleggtittel: Agreement on dual residence for children
